@primusroseblood,							~saisei A landing craft made its way toward the Docking Bay, an Uguisu class shuttle. The Uguisu was a modified Fukubukuro class shuttle, modified for use in horrid conditions. Fitted with Radiant Armor and Shields, Kage Cloaking Device, and Void Null Emitters, it was a defensive power house packaged into a very small ship. The insignia on the hull marked it as a neutral courier and aid vessel belonging to the Nightingale, its transponder keyed to allow for safe passage from those who were honorable.

Going through its maneuvers, it soon landed, and the cargo door at its rear opened to allow the passengers to disembark, one of whom was a man known only to a select few beyond Rokugan Prime -- or as the Nightingale called it Ningen-do Prime.

(The Craft is open for any to use as their means of transportation)

"Beneath the cold stars' gleam,
A warrior stands alone,
Silent as a dream,
His heart a stone, yet it does roam,
To distant fields, where love once shone.

In battles fought and won,
His sword has claimed its due,
Yet when the day is done,
His thoughts stray far, to skies of blue,
Where tender words and vows were true.

But duty's chains hold tight,
And honor's path is clear,
He marches through the night,
Towards the dawn, with naught but fear,
That love will fade, and disappear.

Still, in his soul's deep well,
The longing will not die,
He knows too well the spell,
Of gentle hands and whispered sigh,
For which he fights, though none know why."

"Under the cherry trees bloom,
Where the winds whisper low,
A samurai finds his room,
In the quiet after the glow.

His sword rests by his side,
No longer stained by strife,
In the stillness, he confides,
The peaceful rhythms of life.

Moonlight on his armor gleams,
Yet no battles call tonight,
He drifts in tranquil dreams,
Bathed in the silver light.

The worlds burdens lift away,
As the nightingale softly sings,
And in this moment, he may,
Feel the peace that morning brings.

No enemies, no fears,
Just the gentle rustle of leaves,
In the twilight of his years,
He finds the peace he believes.

For in the heart of war,
A samurai seeks this grace,
To rest when the fight is oer,
And to know a peaceful place."

Scene 1: The Gathering of the Clans

The curtain opens to reveal a clearing in the forest. Nezumi from various clans each distinguished by their unique colors and markings gather in a circle, chittering nervously. They bow and greet each other with exaggerated respect.

Chieftain Riktikkik: (stepping forward) The time has come, brave Nezumi! The dark spirits encroach on our lands, and the ancient city must be reclaimed! Who among us has the courage to face these dangers?

The Nezumi actors chatter and squeak excitedly. One by one, they step forward, showing off their courage with exaggerated gestures some brandishing crude weapons, others puffing out their chests.

Scene 2: The Perilous Path

The scene shifts as the backdrop changes to a perilous ravine, with narrow paths winding between jagged rocks. The Nezumi actors move cautiously, their exaggerated sneaking movements.

Brave Nezumi: (whispering loudly) Watch your step! The ground is treacherous, and the shadows... they whisper!

Suddenly, a large puppet representing a menacing creature emerges from the side of the stage, operated by two Nezumi actors in black. The Nezumi warriors scatter in panic, some leaping over obstacles, others hiding behind rocks, only to reemerge with bold cries of defiance.
@Muddy Paw Troop Tribe,					~7k4 athletics tn15 raise1

Scene 3: The Battle for the Lost City

The backdrop now reveals the ruins of an ancient Nezumi city. The stone pillars and crumbling walls are covered in vines, and the air is thick with tension. The Nezumi warriors gather at the edge of the stage, preparing for the final battle.

Chieftain Riktikkik: (raising his weapon) Today, we fight for our ancestors! We fight for our future! For the Nezumi!

A grand battle ensues, with the actors miming combat with exaggerated, acrobatic movements. The monster puppet returns, now joined by others, creating a chaotic scene. The Nezumi actors perform daring leaps and flips, displaying their agility as they "defeat" the monstrous creatures one by one.
@Muddy Paw Troop Tribe,					~5k3 perform dance tn15

Scene 4: The Return of the Ancestors

As the last creature falls, the Nezumi cheer in unison, their victory clear. The ruins transform props and lighting change to show the city being restored, the vines receding and the walls strengthening.

Ancestor Spirit: (a ghostly puppet descending from above) You have honored us, brave Nezumi. The city is founded once more. Rejoice, for your courage shall be remembered!

The Nezumi actors bow deeply to the spirit, then begin a joyful dance, celebrating their victory. The dance is lively, with the actors spinning and twirling, tails and whiskers flicking with each movement. The music is fast-paced, featuring traditional drums and flutes, but with a playful, almost mischievous tone befitting the Nezumi.
@Muddy Paw Troop Tribe,					~6k3 perform: oratory raise1 tn15

Final Scene: The Feast

The stage transitions to a scene of feasting. Nezumi actors mime eating, drinking, and sharing stories of their adventure, their movements exaggerated and full of humor. The Chieftain raises a cup.

Chieftain Riktikkik: (with a wide, toothy grin) Tonight, we celebrate! For we have faced the darkness and emerged victorious. Tomorrow, we rebuild! But tonight, we feast!

The curtain falls as the Nezumi actors continue their dance, the stage filled with laughter and the sounds of merriment.

Epilogue:

As the curtain rises once more, the stage is dark, with only the Chieftain standing in the center, illuminated by a single spotlight.

Chieftain Riktikkik: (solemnly) And so, the tale of the Courageous Nezumi comes to an end. But remember, in the darkest of times, the Nezumi spirit never falters. We fight, we dance, we survive!

The curtain falls again, and the play ends with the sound of squeaking laughter echoing through the theater.
